About the Company
Online Services
Products
Reviews


Inspired by companies like Beck’s Prime, Southwest Airlines and some other honest institutions, Allied Home Warranty (AHW) claims that their company was started to serve homeowners as a resource that can be used for the smooth running of their homes.? 


AHW is a company that has a lot more to offer than just warranty products. Some of the other services they offer are pest and termite control, home rekeying, home alarm installation, landscaping, mortgage refinancing, AC / heater tuning and a lot more. The company has a full time customer service facility, however after-hour requests have an additional fee.?The company hosts a well maintained website that offers all the basic online services required by customers. Plan details, sample contracts, facilities to sign up and become members and purchase plans, place requests etc can be done through their website.?


For homeowners, the plans are as follows:Basic PlanPremium Plan (Higher coverageBoth plans charge a service call fee of $50?For realtors too, AHW has two different plans to offer:
Buyer’s PlanSeller’s PlanThese plans have features similar to the homeowner’s plans. However they have a few additional benefits. AHW claims that homes with their plans sell 50% faster and avoid unnecessary delays.?The New Construction plan is a unique product by AHW that is designed to cover newly constructed homes. The price starts at $595 for a term of 4 years. Such plans are meant for houses whose Builder’s warranty has already expired.

 












