 WARRANTY BUYER BEWARE: I have recently purchased a new home and received one year of home warranty from Allied. So far we have made three service requests (for $60 a piece). Long story short for the first two was that the items needing repair were to far gone but they would be happy to sell us new systems (furnace and hot water heater). The third is the worst yet. The refrigerator that came with the house failed. A claim was filed and a technician sent (for $60 of course). The technician looked it over and couldn't do the repairs then but had to go back to get approval to do the repairs because he thought it was on the boarder of repair vs getting a payout for the fridge.He said we would get a call back that afternoon. After not hearing anything for a couple days I called allied to inquire on the process and was told that the repair request was approved and they were trying to get a hold of the service technician to schedule the repairs. Allied would call back me that evening to follow up. No call back. A couple of days pass by and I call to inquire again about the progress of the claim. Im told that the claim is delayed because they can not contact the service technician but the operator Im speaking with will get ahold of the technician and personally get back to me that evening. No call. I call yet again, with the same expected response...we can t get a hold of the technician. Two weeks after my initial call I am contacted but not about the repairs but a request for a copy of my home inspection. I sent it in and there is no indication of any deficiencies with the refrigerator. I hear nothing. A few days later I call to inquire about the claim and I'm told that the claim has been declined. They claimed that it was a pre existing condition and not covered. How an item in a home that I have just purchased has a pre existing condition is beyond me especially since it was not discovered on the home inspection. But what really gets me is that it took them three weeks to inform me that they won't fix it even though I was told earlier that it would be. Now after being without a fridge for three weeks with a newborn at home (forgot to mention that. That made it even more fun) we get to go get a new fridge out of pocket. Thanks for nothing allied. It really appears that allied is really just a front for their affiliate NRG to sell installation and service of new overpriced systems and appliances. I will be advising my realtor to steer anyone away from allied. Their services (or lack there of) are not worth it. Anyway do yourself a favor and avoid Allied home Warranty. After all they avoid doing anything for you. view lessWARRANTY BUYER BEWARE: I have recently purchased a new home and received one year of home warranty from Allied. So far we have made three service requests (for $60 a piece). Long story short for the first two was that the items needing repair were to far gone but they would be happy to sell us new systems (furnace and hot water heater). The third is the worst yet. The refrigerator that  ... view more 

